# --- whitelist .gitignore --------------------------------------------------
# Public sharing only: the repo intentionally publishes the README, ESPHome
# YAML, secrets template, Python tester, LICENSE, and itself. Everything else
# (notes, captures, secrets, decompiled APK, custom-component scratch, etc.)
# stays local.

# Ignore everything by default. NOTE: no `!*/` here, so only files at the
# repo root that are explicitly re-allowed below get committed. Subdirs
# (custom_components/, docs/, .esphome/, .cursor/, etc.) stay out entirely.
*

# Then re-allow only the files we actually want public.
!.gitignore
!LICENSE
!README.md
!secrets.example.yaml
!trigger4p_esphome.yaml
!test_trigger_from_mac.py

# Belt-and-braces: never commit real secrets even if the rule above changes.
secrets.yaml

# Belt-and-braces: never commit captures or the decompiled APK.
*.pcap
*.pcapng
*.btsnoop
*.apk
TRIGGER ACS Plus_*_APKPure/
.esphome/
.cursor/
__pycache__/
